    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>If David Rockwell finds it so challenging to make the ''facade, lobby, rooms and restaurant'' of a hotel ''all work together'' [''New Hotel on West 56th Street; A Downtown Look in Midtown,'' July 23] then perhaps he should engage someone specially trained for that task.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>If David Rockwell finds it so challenging to make the ''facade, lobby, rooms and restaurant'' of a hotel ''all work together'' [''New Hotel on West 56th Street; A Downtown Look in Midtown,'' July 23] then perhaps he should engage someone specially trained for that task.</p>
        <p>The A.I.A. has a long list of registered professionals who could do the job. I believe they're called architects.</p>
        <p>DANIEL B. DOBKIN  Great Neck, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
